article.headline: Coppin St 75, Howard 66
article.story: BALTIMORE (AP) -- Darryl Proctor had 22 points and 10 rebounds as Coppin State beat Howard 75-66 on Monday night. The win allowed Coppin State (11-12, 11-3 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) to extend its conference lead over second-place Delaware State to a game and a half. The Hornets lost to Morgan State on Monday. Proctor made a number of key plays, finishing with seven offensive rebounds and four steals. He also hit six of eight free throws. Nicholas King and Raheem Scott scored 14 points each for the Eagles, while Henry Colter and Darryl Roberts added nine apiece. Howard (5-17, 2-11), which has lost 11 straight, fell behind 28-9 in the first half before rallying. Reggie Bates (15 points), Will Gant (14 points) and Darek Mitchell (12 points) sparked the Bison's offense by combining for 12 3-pointers. Coppin State saw its lead dwindle to 35-32 at halftime, and the Eagles never could break the game open after that. They made 24 free throws in the second half and hung on for the win.
